Package: repurrrsive
Title: Examples of Recursive Lists and Nested or Split Data Frames
Version: 0.0.0.9001
Authors@R: c(
  person("Jennifer", "Bryan", role=c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "jenny@stat.ubc.ca"),
  person("Charlotte", "Wickham", role = "ctb", 
    email = "cwickham@gmail.com"))
Description: Recursive lists in the form of R objects, JSON, and XML, for use in
    teaching and examples. Examples include color palettes, Game of Thrones
    characters, GitHub users and repos, and entities from the Star Wars universe. 
    Data from the Gapminder package, as a simple data frame and in nested and 
    split forms.
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
License: CC0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1.9000
Suggests:
    gapminder,
    jsonlite,
    purrr,
    rprojroot (>= 1.0-7),
    testthat,
    wesanderson,
    xml2
